history.text: How's it going? Do you like Christopher Nolan films? Have you heard of Inception?
I love Christopher Nolan and I have heard of Inception
Nice! Yeah, well it was a critically-acclaimed film from 2009 that garnered 86% on rotten tomatoes
I have seen his other films like Vertigo and the Dark Knight Trilogy. Will I enjoy this one?
Excuse me I meant to say Memento
I think so. Leonardo DiCaprio stars as a professional thief and actually infiltrates people's minds
One of their targets, Saito, has a particularly "embedded" idea they need to infiltrate so they need to go deep into his subconcious
Sounds like something I would be interested in. Would you call it a psychological thriller?
Possibly. The genre itself is "scientific" but it is definitely a thriller
Are there any other actors in the film I would interested in?
Yeah Joseph Gordon Levitt, Ellen Page, and Tom Hardy all have prominent roles!
The movie will definitely make you think. A lot of people are raving about that
Oh wow I love them all. Tom Hardy being a personal favorite. I love thinking pieces so I would be down in seeing it
He's an accomplice of DiCaprio in this movie so he definitely gets plenty of screentime
Great? How about Joseph Gordon Levitt? What's his role?
He's the main partner of DiCaprio who basically plans and researches the missions
Would you happen to know who the screenwriter of the film is?
I don't but there are a lot of cool scenes that you'll want to watch out for. There's a point in the movie where if you die in a dream you'll end up in "limbo"
that makes a lot of the scenes intense
Cool! Now how long is the movie?
I'm not sure, it doesn't say
Everything critics say though indicates the movie doesn't drag on
So they are in dream of someone else  trying to solve a mystery?

Esentially DiCaprio's character is trying to get back home and in order to he needs to finish one last mission. The person in charge gives him a task where he needs to enter the mind of a competitor and plant in his mind an idea that'll ruin his business
It's an interesting plot especially with Dicaprio's wife haunting him whenever he goes into a dream
Interesting? So he has a tragic backstory? How does the deceased wife have a role in this case?
So his wife died and he is haunted by that because he feels responsible for her death
a lot of what happens in the movie is off of your subscious so she makes appearances

Does she in some form of fashion
help provide information in helping the business?
No, she's actually there to mess up the plans it seems like
Everytime they enter a mission they risk her showing up and messing things up
Oh! She's kind of an antagonist. I heard this film is full of plot twists is that correct?
That is correct! It literally twists and turns on screen
Well thank you for the encouragement! I really will watch this film now. Been holding it off for a while

uid2response.feedback: Thank you for the chat. The other person was really nice and enthusiastic about the film. I was not the one to receive the document
